{"lemma":"هِجْرَة","slug":"هِجْرَة","root":"ه.ج.ر","root_slug":"ه-ج-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ه-ج-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40929","n40938","n40939"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%87%D9%90%D8%AC%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"migration, emigration, immigration"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"departure, exit"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"renunciation, abandonment"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Hijra, Hegira: the flight of the prophet Muhammad and his followers from Mecca to Yathrib (later Medina) in 622 CE"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/hid͡ʒ.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40929","headword_ar":"هَجَرَهُ","root":"hjr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajorN","text_ar":"هَجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hijoraAnN","text_ar":"هِجْرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, K,) or the latter is a simple subst., (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut him off from friendly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loving, communion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intercourse; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waSalahu","text_ar":"وَصَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he forsook,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abandoned, him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaEahu","text_ar":"قَطَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cut him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he ceased to speak to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to associate with him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saramahu","text_ar":"صَرَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Mgh, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaEa kalaAmahu","text_ar":"قَطَعَ كَلَامَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) It is said in the Kur, [iv. 38,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@hojuruwhun~a fiY AlmaDaAjiEK","text_ar":"وَا@هْجُرُوهُنَّ فِى المَضَاجِعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e., ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And cut ye them off from loving intercourse"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the sleeping-places,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in order to obtain their obedience. (Msb.) See also 3. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He left it; forsook it; relinquished it; abandoned it; deserted it; quitted it: abstained from it: neglected it: shunned"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avoided it; was averse from it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarakahu","text_ar":"تَرَكَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, Msb, K, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaDahu","text_ar":"رَفَضَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAraqahu","text_ar":"فَارَقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (B:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agofalahu","text_ar":"اَغْفَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraDa Eanohu","text_ar":"اَعْرَضَ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) namely, a thing to which it was necessary for him to pay frequent attention: (Lth, TA:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ahojarahu","text_ar":"اَهْجَرَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) which latter is of the dial. of Hudheyl: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hujira","text_ar":"هُجِرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was left;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (IKtt.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hijoraAnN","text_ar":"هِجْرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be with the body and with the tongue and with the heart or mind: it is with the first in the passage of the Kur cited above: it may be with any of the three in the Kur, [lxxiii. 10,] where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@hojurohumo hajorFA jamiylFA","text_ar":"وَا@هْجُرْهُمْ هَجْرًا جَمِيلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And avoid thou them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., avoid the associating with them in person, or speaking to them, or entertaining friendship for them in thy heart,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with an avoiding of a becoming kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and it is with all the three in the following ex. in the Kur, [lxxiv. 5,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@lr~ijoza faA@hojuro","text_ar":"وَا@لرِّجْزَ فَا@هْجُرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And idolatry avoid thou"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (B.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajara Al$~iroka","text_ar":"هَجَرَ الشِّرْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajorN","text_ar":"هَجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hijoraAnN","text_ar":"هِجْرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He abstained from,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avoided, polytheism,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the associating of others with God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hijorapF HasanapF","text_ar":"هِجْرَةً حَسَنَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a good manner of abstaining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avoiding"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Lh, K.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA yasomaEuwna AlquroA=na A_il~aA hajorFA","text_ar":"وَلَا يَسْمَعُونَ القُرْا=نَ اـِلَّا هَجْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they hear not the Kur-án save"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with neglect of it, and aversion from it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the reading"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~A hujorFA","text_ar":"الّا هُجْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned by IKt, and his explanation of it,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"save with foul speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"are both said by El-Khattábee to be erroneous. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajara","text_ar":"هَجَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajorN","text_ar":"هَجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went, removed, retired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withdrew himself, to a distance, far away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"far off."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2880},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajara fiY AlS~awomi","text_ar":"هَجَرَ فِى الصَّوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hijoraAnN","text_ar":"هِجْرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He abstained from sexual intercourse in fasting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajara","text_ar":"هَجَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, Fr, S, A, K, &c.,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajara fiY kalaAmihi","text_ar":"هَجَرَ فِى كَلَامِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, Fr, S, &c.,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajorN","text_ar":"هَجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, S, A, Mgh, Msb,) with fet-h, (Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hujorN","text_ar":"هُجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm, (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hij~iyraY","text_ar":"هِجِّيرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) or this is a simple subst., (Lth,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ihojiyraY","text_ar":"اـِهْجِيرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [or this and that which immediately precedes it are intensive inf. ns.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a sick man, Lth, S, Msb, K, or one having the disease termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birosaAm","text_ar":"بِرْسَام"},{"kind":"text","text":", A'Obeyd, A, or having a fever, A'Obeyd, and one sleeping. Fr, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"talked nonsense; talked irrationally"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foolishly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deliriously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Fr, S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and confusedly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hij~iyraY","text_ar":"هِجِّيرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"talking much, and saying what is evil."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb.) In the Kur, [xxiii. 69,] instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tahojuruwna","text_ar":"تَهْجُرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmirFA tahojuruwna","text_ar":"سَامِرًا تَهْجُرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Holding discourse by night, talking irrationally"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foolishly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] I'Ab reads"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuhojiruwna","text_ar":"تُهْجِرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ahojara","text_ar":"اَهْجَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [q. v.,] from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alhujoru","text_ar":"الهُجْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also 4. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajara bihi","text_ar":"هَجَرَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajorN","text_ar":"هَجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dreamed of him"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saw him"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it in sleep:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did so and talked foolishly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deliriously."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","A","Mgh","K","TA","B","Lth","Fr"]},{"entry_id":"n40938","headword_ar":"هُجْرَةٌ","root":"hjr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hijorapN","text_ar":"هِجْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n40939","headword_ar":"هِجْرَةٌ","root":"hjr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajarahu","text_ar":"هَجَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hijoraAnN","text_ar":"هِجْرَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) signifying The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cutting another off from friendly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loving communion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intercourse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cutting one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ceasing to speak to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forsaking, abandoning, deserting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shunning"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avoiding, one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA hijorapa baEoda valaAvK","text_ar":"لَا هِجْرَةَ بَعْدَ ثَلَاثٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There shall be no cutting off from friendly communion after three"},{"kind":"text","text":"nights with their days,]: the meaning is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hajorN","text_ar":"هَجْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waSolN","text_ar":"وَصْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e., such anger as exists between Muslims, or a failing, or falling short, with respect to the duties of society, exclusively of what relates to religion: but the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hijorap","text_ar":"هِجْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of those who follow their own natural desires [in matters of religion], and of innovators [in religion], should continue even as long as they do not repent, and return to the truth. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of cutting another off from friendly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loving communion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intercourse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. See 1, where an ex. occurs.] ―         -b3-  Also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A removal from the desert to the towns"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"villages:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this was its [primary] acceptation with the Arabs: and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forsaking of his country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"district,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, by an inhabitant of the desert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by an inhabitant of a town,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"village,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cultivated district, and taking up his abode in another country"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"district,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, an emigration;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forsaking of one's home and removing to another place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forsaking of a country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"district,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, and removing to another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going forth from one land to another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hujorapN","text_ar":"هُجْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an emigration from the territory of the unbelievers to the territory of the believers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to any place of safety"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refuge on account of religious persecution &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 3, last signification:] a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAjara","text_ar":"هَاجَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.) ―         -b4-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlhijorapN","text_ar":"الهِجْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", peculiarly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The emigration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(for it was really a flight,) of Mohammad, from Mekkeh to Yethrib, which latter was afterwards called El-Medeeneh. Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^oriyxu Alhijorapi","text_ar":"تَاْرِيخُ الهِجْرَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The era of the Hijreh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Flight."},{"kind":"text","text":"The epoch of this era is not the date of the Flight itself, as some have imagined, (for this took place on an uncertain day, most probably the first or second, of the third lunar month of the Arabian year,) but is the first day of the Arabian year in which the Flight happened: and as I believe that all European writers who have attempted to fix it, prior to M. Caussin de Perceval, have erred respecting it, the true date, as shown by him, (see his “ Essai sur l'Histoire des Arabes, ” &c., in the places referred to in the index to that"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2881},{"kind":"text","text":"work,) I think it important here to mention. The first year of the Flight was the two hundred and eleventh year of a period during which the Arabs made use of a defective luni-solar reckoning, making every third year to consist of thirteen lunar months; the others consisting of twelve such months. This mode of reckoning was abolished by Mohammad in the twelfth month of the tenth year of the Flight, at the time of the pilgrimage; whence it appears that the first year of the Flight commenced, most probably, on Monday, the nineteenth of April, A. D. 622; or perhaps on the eighteenth; for the actual appearance of the new moon properly marked its commencement, and, as the new moon happened about sunset on the sixteenth, it may perhaps have been seen on the eve of the eighteenth. According to M. Caussin de Perceval, the first ten years of the Flight commenced at the following periods."},{"kind":"text","text":"1st.\n                        [Mon.]\n                        Apr. 19, 622\n                      \n                     \n                        2nd.\n                        [Sat.]\n                        May 7, 623\n                      \n                     \n                        3rd.\n                        [Th.]\n                        Apr. 26, 624\n                      \n                     \n                        4th.\n                        [Mon.]\n                        Apr. 15, 625\n                      \n                     \n                        5th.\n                        [Sat.]\n                        May. 3, 626\n                      \n                     \n                        6th.\n                        [Th.]\n                        Apr. 23, 627\n                      \n                     \n                        7th.\n                        [Tu.]\n                        Apr. 12, 628\n                      \n                     \n                        8th.\n                        [Mon.]\n                        May. 1, 629\n                      \n                     \n                        9th.\n                        [Fri.]\n                        Apr. 20, 630\n                      \n                     \n                        10th.\n                        [Tu.]\n                        Apr. 9, 631"},{"kind":"text","text":"Thus it appears that the first and fourth and seventh years were of thirteen lunar months each; and the seventh was the last year that was thus augmented: therefore, with the eighth year commenced the reckoning by common lunar years; and from this point we may use the tables which have often been published for finding the periods of commencement of years of the Flight. We must not, however, rely upon the exact accuracy of these tables: for the commencement of the month was generally determined by actual observation of the new moon; not by calculation; and we often find that a year was commenced, according as the place of observation was low or high, or to the east or west of the place to which the calculation is adapted, or according as the sky was obscure or clear, a day later or earlier than that which is indicated in the tables; and in some cases, even two days later. The twelfth day of the third month of the first year of the Flight, the day of Mohammad's arrival at Kubà, was Monday: therefore the first day of the year was most probably the nineteenth of April, as two months of thirty days each, or twenty-nine days each, seldom occur together. But the tenth day of the first month of the sixty-first year, the day on which El-Hoseyn was slain at Kerbelà, was Friday: therefore the first day of that year, at that place, must have been Wednesday, the third of October, A. D. 680; not the first of October, as in most of the published tables above mentioned. (For the principal divisions of the Arabian year when the luni-solar reckoning was instituted, see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamanN","text_ar":"زَمَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")]."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlhijorataAni","text_ar":"الهِجْرَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two emigrations,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flights;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hijorap","text_ar":"هِجْرَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to Abyssinia and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hijorap","text_ar":"هِجْرَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to El-Medeeneh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw Alhijoratayoni","text_ar":"ذُو الهِجْرَتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHaAbap","text_ar":"صَحَابَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or Companions of Mohammad] TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who emigrated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has emigrated, to Abyssinia and to El-Medeeneh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Msb"]}]}}